🛠 Challenge: Fix the Homepage Search Button Issue

The Axe DevTools scan found an issue with the Search icon button on the homepage not having discernible text. This button accompanies two form fields for searching camp locations and dates.

Generally speaking, there are a few things we could do that would make it work better with a screen reader. These techniques would also allow us to pass the WCAG 4.1.2 success criterion for the Search button.

We could:

  • Add an aria-label attribute
  • Add some text content and visually hide it with CSS
  • Use aria-labelledby to reference content from a nearby element via its id attribute (e.g. a heading)
  • Use the title attribute
  • Add a role of none if the element is purely decorative.

Choose a solution and implement the fix so Axe DevTools no longer finds an issue.

🛠 Solution: Fixing the Homepage Search Button

To fix the issues with the Search icon button, we'll add an aria-label attribute with a value of "Submit":

To fix the issues with the search icon button, we'll add an ARIA label of "Submit":

<button
	class="btn-submit btn-lookingglass"
	onclick="javascript: alert('Submitted!');")"
	aria-label="Submit"
>
<button
	class="btn-submit btn-lookingglass"
	onclick="javascript: alert('Submitted!');")"
	aria-label="Submit"
>

📝 Exercise: Fix More Axe DevTools Issues

The Axe DevTools scan found quite a few issues to fix:

A missing HTML lang attribute, SVG images with missing alt descriptions, and more.

Work through solving these issues. You can save the issues related to headings and landmarks for checking with different tools.

Run Axe again as you go, so you get the satisfaction of watching the number of issues drop!
